Larue PredatAR 5.56 Overview The PredatAR 5.56 is designed for those who are searching for a lightweight, ultra-reliable and accurate 5.56 mm NATO rifle for home-defense, competition-shooting or hunting. The PredatAR takes the highly accurate OBR 5.56 “Lite” design, and lightens it in every possible way with the least possible impact to the accuracy that the standard OBR is known for. By contouring the barrel, skeletonizing the handguard, lowering and simplifying the upper rail, and using a low-profile gas block, we were able to reduce roughly 2 pounds from the standard OBR 5.56 rifle. 

The barrels are Stainless Steel, lightweight-profiled, Wylde chambered and feature polygonal rifling in a 1/8 twist rate. All barrels are threaded in ½ x 28, with an A2 flash hider attached* (other muzzle devices can be added at an additional cost). The handguards on the PredatAR extend out 14.75”, to suit a larger range of shooting styles. The zero-MOA upper rail provides plenty of room for weapon-mounted night-vision day/night combinations. Both the upper and lower are CNC-machined from billet 7075-T6, for the optimum fit and consistency. Even though we lightened certain features, there is still additional material in strategic areas to achieve maximum accuracy. 

Each rifle ships with one, 3” long, MIL-STD-1913 detachable rail section. Comes with a 6-position Magpul MOE Stock and LaRue medium A-PEG™ Grip. The Bolt Carriers are hand-polished hard-chrome with max-staked carrier keys, with Texas-Spec Bolt assemblies. The lower assembly has the proven Geissele Two-Stage trigger. XTRAXN™ is a proprietary chamber feature added to reduce frictional forces caused by pressure-expanded cartridge cases bearing against chamber walls. Facilitates reliable extraction through a wide range of temperature / chamber pressure extremes. XTRAXN™ extends extractor life, while having no effect on the firearm's accuracy. All this, and it dovetails well with the OBR's world-famous accuracy. 

Caliber: 5.56 x 45 mm NATO Rifle Weight: 6.25 lb. (based on 16.1” barrel version, unloaded without optics) Barrel Length: 16.1“ Barrel Material: Stainless Steel, Blackened. title: For Sale:  Soviet Russian AKS-74 1980 RARE!!!
postcontent: This is a super-rare 1980-dated Soviet Russian Izhmash AKS-74. No kits like this were ever imported en masse. The parts used were sourced from a rare European deact kit and reassembled here on a NDS-2SF receiver using a pulled Bulgarian barrel and Tapco G2 trigger group. The kit is one of maybe 2 or 3 1980-dated Russian 74 kits known to exist in the US. The trunion, top cover, and gas tube are original matching numbers. Unfortunately, the matching bolt carrier did not make it with this kit. A later Russian Bolt/carrier combo are in its stead. There are several nuances present with this build that you won't find in a "cloned " pieced-together Russian AKS-74. The stock assy has Russian proofs, the mold numbers on the barrel hardware are unique when compared to the common '83 kits, the top cover is the earlier-style, etc

postcontent:
This is a model 1842 U.S. Percussion (smoothbore) Musket reproduction. It is stamped as an 1846 Production model. The model 1842 was produced in great numbers by both Harpers Ferry and Springfield Armories from 1844 to 1855. This reproduction is true to the original measurements, with a 42" barrel and a total length of 58 inches. title: For Sale:  Flare Pistol 26.5mm - Unfired w/adapters, holster & cartridges
postcontent:
This 26.5mm flare pistol was made in 1985. It was manufactured in Poland and is an almost exact copy of the HK P2A1 pistol. The serial numbers on the frame match those on the barrel. This particular one is somewhat unusual in that it is in new/unfired condition. Most of these were issued before they were imported into the US, and they typically show the signs of that use.

 Pistol comes with it's original cleaning rod & lanyard, a weather resistant flap style holster with shoulder carry strap. Holster can carry the pistol, cleaning rod, 26.5mm flare cartridges, sub caliber adapters, and even a box of .22 ammo (see pictures).

Additionally there is an adapter that allows for any .22 short, long or long rifle ammo to be safely fired, and another adapter for firing the less expensive 12 gauge flare cartridges. Please note that you must never attempt to fire any 12 gauge ammo other than flare cartridges as to do so would be disastrous.

Finally the following ammo is included:
(2) 26.5mm orange smoke shells
(2) 26.5mm red rain shells
(2) 26.5mm brilliant white parachute illumination shells
(1) sealed package of Orion 12 gauge super red flares 
(150) rounds .22LR ammo - 100 rounds Mini-Mag, 50 rounds Aguila Super Maximum & 50 rounds Aguila Sub Sonic Sniper with special 60 grain bullet 

Price is $225. Pickup in Brandon. Because .22 adapter turns this flare pistol into a firearm when installed - you must be 21 to purchase. Thanks for looking.

title: For Sale:   Winchester 1892 Take Down Rifle OBCBFM 25-20 WCF
postcontent: Offered is this rare 1892 Winchester take down rifle in 25-20 WCF. It was made in 1902, it has a 24 inch octagon barrel with a shootable bore, I rate the bore a 6 on a 1 to 10 scale, good rifling with some use wear. The barrel and magazine retain full blue coverage, the barrel is a dark plum blue. The receiver is mechanically excellent and has that very desirable "smooth as glass" operation when you cycle the bolt. This smooth operation was a hallmark of Winchester's early rifles when they spent the time to hand finish the internal working parts - nice! It feeds, chambers and ejects smoothly and properly. There is little original blue remaining, mostly a nice dark plum patina. The screw slots are still sharp and not buggered up. The take down is snug and functions correctly. The wood is tight and solid on both the forend and buttstock. Overall this Winchester is all original and correct and in excellent operating condition. It has not been cleaned or fooled with, a rare, vintage Winchester for your collection.

postcontent: I have a very rare Bulgarian Arsenal  SLR-96 7.62x39 caliber semi auto 16 inch barrel Kalashnikov AK-47 parts kit that are no longer imported.This kit will need a milled receiver which can be had on the net for around $300 and up This is a very rare kit as most of these rifles were sold complete.The SLR-96 is one of the BEST 'Real Military Arsenal' AK's EVER imported into the USA (Milled-Receiver & Steyr Hammer-Forged Barrel)Between (1993-1994),  the SLR-96 is considered one of the most desireable of the AK imports.
